  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I can't remember much.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember, like, the few episodes that I said that were about him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I actually remember one other thing about him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was probably also [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in '39, where, in the summer, he took my brother and me out somewhere [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to a beach, which I remember till today.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My brother's name is Arieh.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name is Raveh today.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He Hebrew-tized his name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He changed his name to Hebrew, and he's Raveh.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He lives in Israel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He has a family-- three children, a daughter and two sons.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] He is almost two years younger than me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] About maybe going back to what I remember about the personalities, as I say, I know from-- from what I-- from stories, that, and as I mentioned before, my father grew up in Janusz Korczak's orphanage, and he got a very well education there.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that's what that I had said that I remembered, that he took us to the beach in that summer of probably 1939.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That probably was the last summer before the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He took us there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a very good time and we enjoyed, and I remember it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] My father, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] he-- he was-- he was well-educated in Janusz Korczak, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] but he didn't have-- he wanted to continue studies.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But because they were poor, he couldn't continue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But from friends that-- his colleagues that I met years after-- everybody used to tell me the same thing, that how smart and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [SOBBING] and bright my father was.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
